st aired. Should be omitted if the same country as country of origin above. -->\n| first_aired              = {{start date|2020|3|12}}\n| last_aired               = {{end date|present}}\n| preceded_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that preceded another in a television lineup. -->\n| followed_by              = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that followed another in a television lineup. -->\n| related                  = <!-- To be used only for remakes, spin-offs, and adaptations -->\n| website                  = http://program.tving.com/tvn/doctorlife/\n}}\n\n'''''Hospital Playlist'''''<ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=781zc9M2HBw|title=[\ud2f0\uc800] \uc751\ub2f5\ud558\ub77c \uc81c\uc791\uc9c4\uc774 \uc758\ub4dc\ub97c \ud558\ub294 \uc774\uc720\ub294? \uc2ac\uae30\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc758\uc0ac\uc0dd\ud65c coming soon! \uc2ac\uae30\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc758\uc0ac\uc0dd\ud65c Hospital Playlist EP.0|website=[[YouTube]]|publisher=tvN DRAMA|language=ko|accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref> ({{Korean|\uc2ac\uae30\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc758\uc0ac\uc0dd\ud65c||Seulgiroun Euisasaenghal|lit='''''Wise Doctor Life'''''}}) is a [[Korean drama|South Korean television series]] starring [[Jo Jung-suk]], [[Yoo Yeon-seok]], [[Jung Kyung-ho (actor, born 1983)|Jung Kyung-ho]], [[Kim Dae-myung]] and Jeon Mi-do.  It is the second installment of the ''Wise Life'' series, following ''[[Prison Playbook]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/the-wise-series-is-back-this-time-at-a-hospital-139332.html|date=March 5, 2020|work=[[HanCinema]]|title=The 'Wise' Series Is Back, This Time at a Hospital|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref> It airs on [[TVN (South Korean TV channel)|tvN]] every Thursday at 21:00 ([[Time in South Korea|KST]]) starting from March 12, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Ji-won|last=Choi|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200310000896&np=1&mp=1|title=Star producer of \u2018Reply\u2019 series returns with \u2018Hospital Playlist\u2019|date=March 10, 2020|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|lang=ko|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Esther|last=Chung|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3074821|title=High hopes for \u2018Hospital Playlist\u2019 as it makes its premiere tonight|date=March 12, 2020|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|lang=ko|accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Gyu-lee|last=Lee|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2020/03/688_286142.html|title=TvN series 'Hospital Playlist' off to good start|date=March 13, 2020|website=[[The Korea Times]]|lang=ko|accessdate=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Synopsis==\n''Hospital Playlist'', which mostly takes place at Yulje Medical Center, tells the story of five doctors who have been friends since they entered medical school in 1999.\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Jo Jung-suk]] as Lee Ik-joon\n:A professor of general surgery.\n* [[Yoo Yeon-seok]] as Ahn Jung-won\n:A professor of pediatric surgery.\n* [[Jung Kyung-ho (actor, born 1983)|Jung Kyung-ho]] as Kim Joon-wan\n:A professor of cardiothoracic surgery.\n* [[Kim Dae-myung]] as Yang Seok-hyung\n:A professor of obstetrics and gynecology surgery\n* Jeon Mi-do as Chae Song-hwa<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/jeon-mi-do-wins-audiences-love-and-attention-139303.html|date=March 4, 2020|work=[[HanCinema]]|title=Jeon Mi-do Wins Audiences' Love and Attention|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n:A professor of neurological surgery.\n\n===Supporting===\n{{colbegin}}\n====Doctors====\n* Jo Seung-yeon as Joo Jun\n* Jung Moon-sung as Do Jae-hak\n* Moon Tae-yoo as Yong Seok-min\n* [[Shin Hyun-bin]] as Jang Gyeo-wool\n* [[Kim Jun-han]] as Ahn Chi-hong\n* Choi Young-joon as Bong Gwang-hyun\n* [[Ahn Eun-jin]] as Choo Min-ha<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/ahn-eun-jin-to-star-in-hospital-playlist-136562.html|date=December 9, 2019|work=[[HanCinema]]|title=Ahn Eun-jin to Star in \"Hospital Playlist\"|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* Ha Yoon-kyung as Heo Sun-bin\n* [[Kim Hye-in]] as Myung Eun-won<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/kim-hye-in-to-star-in-hospital-playlist-136680.html|date=December 12, 2019|work=[[HanCinema]]|title=Kim Hye-in to Star in \"Hospital Playlist\"|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* Choi Young-woo as Cheon Myung-tae\n* Shin Do-hyun as Bae Joon-hee\n* Lee Ji-hoon as Doctor\n* Jeon Kwang-jin as Jong Se-hyuk\n\n====Nurses====\n* Kim Soo-jin as Song Soo-bin\n* Yoon Hye-ri as So Yi-hyun\n* Yang Jo-ah as Hwang Jae-shin\n* Lee Noh-ah as Lee Young-ha\n\n====Others====\n* [[Kim Hae-sook]] as Jung Ro-sa\n* [[Kim Kap-soo]] as Joo Jong-soo\n* [[Sung Dong-il]] as Jung-won's eldest brother\n* Jo Yi-hyun as Jang Yoon-bok<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/jo-yi-hyun-in-hospital-playlist-and-how-to-buy-a-friend-139337.html|date=March 5, 2020|work=[[HanCinema]]|title=Jo Yi-hyun in \"Hospital Playlist\" and \"How to Buy a Friend\"|accessdate=March 23, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Bae Hyun-sung]] as Jang Hong-do\n* Park Seung-tae as brain cancer patient\n* Kim Dae-gon as Gal Ba-ram's husband\n* Jung Yu-min as Jung Eun-bin\n* Kwak Sun-young as Lee Ik-sun\n* [[Moon Hee-kyung]] as Seok-hyung's mother\n* Nam Myung-ryeol as Seok-hyung's father\n* Jung Doo-gyeom as Go Young-min\n* Heo Soon-mi as Kim Jae-young\n* Yoon Byung-hee as Kim Jae-young's husband\n{{colend}}\n\n===Special appearances===\nThe following guest appearances are adapted from the closing credits.\n{{colbegin}}\n* Hwang Young-hee as liver transplant patient's mother (Ep. 1)<ref name=\"guests\">{{Cite web|first=Na-kyung|last=Kim|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/202004150841I|title=\u2018\uc2ac\uae30\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc758\uc0ac\uc0dd\ud65c\u2019 \ubab0\uc785\ub3c4 UP\uc2dc\ud0a8 \uc54c\ucc2c \ud2b9\ubcc4\ucd9c\uc5f0 \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5|date=April 15, 2020|website=Hankyung|lang=ko|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Yeom Hye-ran]] as Min-young's mother (Ep. 1)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* [[Kim Sung-kyun]] as Jung-won's second eldest brother (Ep. 1)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* [[Ye Ji-won]] as Jung-won's eldest sister (Ep. 1)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* [[Oh Yoon-ah]] as Jung-won's second eldest sister (Ep. 1)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* Park Hyoung-soo as Lawyer Pyeon (Ep. 1)\n* Jung Jae-sung as Chief of Neurosurgery (Ep. 1)<ref>{{Cite web|first=Woo-joo|last=Lee|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2020/03/13/2020031300762.html|title='\uc2ac\uae30\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc758\uc0ac\uc0dd\ud65c' \uc815\uc7ac\uc131, \ud2b9\ubcc4\ucd9c\uc5f0 \uc7a5\uc778\uc758 \uc874\uc7ac\uac10...\"\uc2e0\uc6d0\ud638PD\uc640\uc758 \uc778\uc5f0\"|date=March 13, 2020|website=News Chosun|lang=ko|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n* Kim Kook-hee as Gal Ba-ram (Ep. 2)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* [[Kim Sung-cheol]] as No Jin-hyung (Ep. 2)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* Kim Han-jong as Gong Hyung-woo (Ep. 2)<ref>{{Cite web|first=Yoon-mi|last=Lee|url=http://www.etoday.co.kr/news/view/1872623|title=\uc2ac\uae30\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc758\uc0ac\uc0dd\ud65c \ub4f1\uc7a5\uc778\ubb3c, \uc2e0\ub3c4\ud604 \uc774\uc5b4 '\uac10\ube75\uc0dd\ud65c' \uc2dd\uad6c \ub4f1\uc7a5|date=March 19, 2020|website=Etoday|lang=ko|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Lee Soo-geun]] as radio host (Ep. 3, voice only)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* Eun Ji-won as radio host (Ep. 3, voice only)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* Shim Dal-gi as Chan-hyung's mother (Ep. 3)<ref>{{Cite web|first=Jae-wan|last=Go|url=http://www.sportschosun.com/news/utype.htm?id=202004100100087440005224&ServiceDate=20200410|title=[SC\ucd08\uc810] '\uc2ac\uc758\uc0dd' \uc131\ub3d9\uc77c\u2192\uc5fc\ud61c\ub780\u2192\uace0\uc544\ub77c\u2026\uaca9\uc774 \ub2e4\ub978 '\ud2b9\ubcc4\ucd9c\uc5f0'|date=April 10, 2020|website=Sports Chosun|lang=ko|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n* Gi Eun-se as Yuk Hye-jung (Ep. 3)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* [[Go Ara]] as Go Ara (Ep. 5\u20136)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n* Kim Dong-kyu (Ep. 5, voice only)<ref name=\"guests\" />\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nScreenwriter [[Lee Woo-jung]] and director [[Shin Won-ho (director)|Shin Won-ho]] previously worked together on the critically acclaimed ''[[Reply (TV series)|Reply]]'' anthology series (2012\u201316) as well as the hit black comedy series ''[[Prison Playbook]]'' (2017\u201318).<ref>{{Cite web|first=Na-kyung|last=Kim|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/201912038551I|title='\uc2ac\uae30\ub85c\uc6b4 \uc758\uc0ac\uc0dd\ud65c', \uc774\ubc88\uc5d4 \ubcd1\uc6d0\uc774\ub2e4\u2026\ub300\ubcf8\ub9ac\ub529 \ud604\uc7a5 \uacf5\uac1c|date=December 3, 2019|website=Hankyung|lang=ko|accessdate=January 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Original soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Hospital Playlist OST\n| type         = [[soundtrack]]\n| artist       = Various Artists\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2020\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Soundtrack]]\n| language     = {{hlist|[[Korean language|Korean]]|[[English language|English]]}}\n| label        = {{hlist|Studio Maeum C|Egg is Coming|[[Genie Music|Genie]]|[[Stone Music Entertainment|Stone]]}}\n| producer     = \n}}\n\n===Part 1===\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Released on {{start date|2020|3|13}}\n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Lonely Night\n| note1 = \n| lyrics1 = [[Kim Tae-won]]\n| music1 = Kim Tae-won\n| extra1 = [[Kwon Jin-ah]]{{efn|Original song by [[Boohwal]], released in 1997.}}\n| length1 = 4:04\n| title2 = Lonely Night\n| note2 = Inst.\n| music2 = Kim Tae-won\n| length2 = 4:04\n| total_length = 8:08\n}}\n\n===Part 2===\n{{tracklist\n| headline = Released on {{start date|2020|3|20}}\n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Introduce Me a Good Person\n| note1 = \uc88b\uc740 \uc0ac\ub78c \uc788\uc73c\uba74 \uc18c\uac1c\uc2dc\ucf1c\uc918 \n| lyrics1 = Kim Hee-tam\n| music1 = [[Jung Jae-hyung]]\n| extra1 = [[Joy (singer)|Joy]] ([[Red Velvet (band)|Red Velvet]]){{efn|Original song by Basis, released in 1996.}}\n| length1 = 3:08\n| title2 = Introduce Me a Good Person\n| no